Vehicles between 15 and 28 tonnes are now able to access the valley with Council permission, under stop/slow conditions.

As the area remains a construction site, safety procedures must be followed.

For vehicles between 15 and 28 tonnes to access the site:

  • Please email the Manager Transport and Public Access, Nicole Hume at nhume@bmcc.nsw.gov.au with at least two working days’ notice to obtain a permit for the heavy vehicle access.
  • A permit will be required to be carried and shown to traffic control on site. Traffic controllers will then coordinate access through the site.

Please note that if the same vehicle needs to access the valley multiple times, only one permit will be required. Vehicles over 15 tonnes that are not scheduled to enter the valley will be turned back to ensure safety is maintained on site.

Portable traffic lights will allow motorists to pass in one direction at a time.

Motorists are advised to allow approximately 5 minutes of additional travel time.

Road closures and clearways will be in place for a planned Police Operation in Redfern.

Road closures:

  • From 7.30am to 12.30pm sections of Cleveland St between Regent St and Chalmers St, George St, Order Pl, Pitt St, Renwick St, Short St, Stirling St and William St will be closed. Managed residential access will be maintained at some locations
  • From 7.30am to 3.30pm George St and Pitt St will be closed between Cleveland St and James St.

Special event clearways will be in effect from 6am to 3.30pm on sections of Chalmers St, George St and Pitt St.

Clearways are strict no-parking zones for all vehicle types and apply even to local residents and TfNSW Mobility Scheme Permit holders. Check signs carefully as vehicles left in clearways will be towed and a fee applies. If your vehicle is towed, you can search your vehicle registration at the Find My Car website to find its new location, or alternatively call 132 701 to speak to an operator.
